15 decentralized system - 
15.2 decentralized network* [NISTIR] - a network configuration where there are multiple authorities that serve as a centralized hub for a subsection of participants. Since some participants are behind a centralized hub, the loss of that hub will prevent those participants from communicating.
16 digital asset - [307]
[NISTIR] - any asset that is purely digital, or is a digital representation of a physical asset.
16.2 digest* [NISTIR] - see "hash digest".
17 digital signature - [307] data which, when appended to a digital document, enable the user of the document to authenticate its origin and integrity [ISO 14641:2018, 3.17].
[NISTIR] a cryptographic technique that utilizes asymmetric-keys to determine authenticity (i.e., users can verify that the message was signed with a private key corresponding to the specified public key), non-repudiation (a user cannot deny having sent a message) and integrity (that the message was not altered during transmission).
17.2 signature* - 
18 distributed application ledger application blockchain application (DApp) - [307] application that runs on a distributed system.
19 distributed ledger - [307] ledger that is shared and synchronized in a distributed manner.
20 distributed ledger technology (abbreviated as DLT) - [307] technology that enables the operation and use of distributed ledgers. 
21 distributed ledger network - [307] network within a distributed ledger system.
22 distributed ledger system - [307] system that implements a distributed ledger.
