27 double spending - 
27.2 double spend (problem)* [NISTIR] - transacting with the same set of digital assets more than once. This is a problem which has plagued many digital money systems, and a problem that most blockchain networks are designed to prevent.
27.3 double spend (attack)* [NISTIR] - an attack where a blockchain network user attempts to explicitly double spend a digital asset.
28 entity - [307] item inside or outside an information and communication technology system, such as a person, an organization, a device, a subsystem, or a group of such items that has recognizably distinct existence.
29 fault tolerance
30 fork - [307] creation of different version of a distributed ledger originating from a common starting point with a single history.
31 genesis block - [307] the first (nature) block in a blockchain.
